# Clutch Fantasy Sports — Cowork Instructions

## Project Overview
Season-long fantasy sports platform. Golf-first, multi-sport by design. Clean, modern UX — think Sleeper's polish with Fantrax's depth plus AI coaching.

## Dev Environment
- **Frontend:** React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS → `http://localhost:5173`
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express → `http://localhost:3001`
- **Start frontend:** `cd frontend && npm run dev`
- **Start backend:** `cd backend && npm run dev`
- **Vite proxy:** `/api` requests proxy to backend on port 3001

## Brand System

### Colors (CSS Variables + Tailwind)
- **Background:** Light `#FAFAF6` / Dark `#0E1015` → `bg-[var(--bg)]`
- **Surface:** Light `#FFFFFF` / Dark `#1A1D26`
- **Text primary:** Light `#1A1A1A` / Dark `#EEEAE2`
- **Blaze (primary/CTA):** `#F06820` → `blaze`, `blaze-hot`, `blaze-deep`
- **Slate (nav/headers):** `#1E2A3A` → `slate`, `slate-mid`, `slate-light`
- **Field (success/green):** `#0D9668` → `field`, `field-bright`
- **Crown (premium/gold):** `#D4930D` → `crown`, `crown-bright`
- **Live red:** `#E83838` → `live-red`

### Typography (Tailwind classes)
- **Display** (headlines, titles, CTAs): `font-display` → Bricolage Grotesque 700-800
- **Body** (readable text): `font-body` → DM Sans 400-700
- **Data** (scores, stats, numbers): `font-mono` → JetBrains Mono 400-700
- **Editorial** (accent, pull quotes): `font-editorial` → Instrument Serif 400i (always italic)

### Theme
- **Light-first** — Clutch is the only fantasy platform defaulting to light mode
- Dark mode via `class="dark"` on `<html>`, toggled by ThemeContext
- Use `dark:` Tailwind prefix for dark mode variants
- CSS variables defined in `frontend/src/index.css`

## UI/UX Rules
1. **Season-long first** — optimize for league experience, not DFS
2. **Clean over cluttered** — when in doubt, simplify
3. **Mobile-responsive** — every page must work on phone (test at 375px)
4. **No gambling aesthetic** — no flashing numbers, no odds, no sportsbook cards
5. **Commissioner is king** — commissioner tools are priority
6. **Progressive disclosure** — default UX is simple, depth is one click away

## Component Patterns
- Pages live in `frontend/src/pages/`
- Reusable components in `frontend/src/components/` (22 category folders)
- Common UI: `components/common/` (Button, Card, Input, Modal, Badge, Chip, Avatar, Tabs)
- Layout: Navbar + MobileNav (bottom), responsive sidebar
- Data fetching: Custom hooks in `frontend/src/hooks/`
- API calls: `frontend/src/services/api.js` (100+ methods)
- Auth: `useAuth()` from AuthContext
- Theme: `useTheme()` from ThemeContext
- Sport context: `useSport()` from SportContext

## Styling Conventions
- Tailwind-first — avoid custom CSS unless necessary
- Border radius: `rounded-card` (cards), `rounded-button` (buttons), `rounded-badge` (badges)
- Shadows: `shadow-card`, `shadow-card-hover`, glow effects for emphasis
- Animations: `animate-pulse-soft`, `animate-slide-down`, `animate-fade-in`, `animate-scale-up`
- Glass morphism layers for overlay surfaces
- Tinted card backgrounds: golf green, NFL orange, news gray, rating gold, AI purple

## Key Visual Components
- **NeuralCluster** — Animated SVG brain (AI coach visual signature). Sizes: sm/md/lg
- **SgRadarChart** — Custom SVG 5-axis radar chart (no external library)
- **AuroraBackground** — Animated background (dark mode only)
- **Coach Briefing** — Template-based, top of dashboard

## Prediction System Visual Rules
- Cards look like community polls, NOT sportsbook props
- No green/red flashing numbers or casino animations
- Use "Calls" not "Picks", "Predictions" not "Bets"

## Screenshot Verification Checklist
When verifying UI changes, check:
- [ ] Light mode appearance
- [ ] Dark mode appearance (toggle via theme button in nav)
- [ ] Mobile responsive (375px width)
- [ ] Text readability and contrast
- [ ] Brand color consistency
- [ ] Font family correctness (display vs body vs mono vs editorial)
- [ ] Interactive states (hover, focus, active)

## File Structure Quick Reference
```
frontend/src/
├── App.jsx          — 70+ routes
├── main.jsx         — Entry (providers)
├── index.css        — CSS variables, brand system
├── pages/           — 73 page components
├── components/      — 176 components (22 categories)
├── services/api.js  — REST client (100+ methods)
├── context/         — Auth, Theme, Notification, Sport, Onboarding
├── hooks/           — Custom React hooks
└── utils/           — Helpers
```

## What NOT to Do
- Don't use raw provider names (ESPN, DataGolf) in user-facing UI — brand as "Clutch"
- Don't add gambling language (picks, bets, odds, lock it in)
- Don't break existing Tailwind class patterns with inline styles
- Don't add new npm dependencies without checking if existing ones cover the need
- Don't modify backend code — Cowork focuses on frontend visual work
